title: Online Credit Card Fraud by Postcode, United Kingdom, 2009
name: Online Credit Card Fraud by Postcode, United Kingdom, 2009
description:
The research comes from industry body The 3rd Man which provides fraud analysis and consultancy services to large UK retailers such as Argos, Halfords and Ticketmaster and monitors a fifth of the UK's card transactions.

They analyzed 85m transactions from August 2008-August 2009, identifying card frauds across the UK by postcode. Interestingly, there are hotspots of activity - and at least £85m in identifiable 'bad' transactions. 

The data is geocoded by postcode and includes number of transactions, Total value in £, number of goods ordered, number of frauds, fraud value in £, and percent(%) of good and bad transactions.

author.source: Guardian News and Media Limited / the3rdman
